description: Turns on GuardDuty monitoring of the specified member accounts. Use this operation to restart monitoring of accounts that you stopped monitoring with the StopMonitoringMembers operation.

parameters.name: DetectorId
parameters.description: The unique ID of the detector of the GuardDuty administrator account associated with the member accounts to monitor. To find the detectorId in the current Region, see the Settings page in the GuardDuty console, or run the ListDetectors API.

parameters.name: AccountIds
parameters.description: A list of account IDs of the GuardDuty member accounts to start monitoring. (string) ---

nested_items.name: UnprocessedAccounts
nested_items.description: A list of objects that contain the unprocessed account and a result string that explains why it was unprocessed.

nested_items.name: AccountId
nested_items.description: The Amazon Web Services account ID.

nested_items.name: Result
nested_items.description: A reason why the account hasn't been processed.
